        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 2:47PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles north of Forest City, or 4 miles north of Bostic, moving east
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Forest City, Spindale, Belwood, Lawndale, Fallston, Polkville,
Bostic, Casar, Kingstown, and Ellenboro.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
